is could clarify what's going on with the coverage generation issue. Let's explore this further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering annotation options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether to add the `@RegisterForReflection` annotation to the test class. It seems like it would enable native deserialization by allowing the readObject method to be accessed. However, I'm torn since the guidelines say, “Never generate, write, or modify reachability metadata,” yet they don’t specifically mention annotations. I’d prefer to avoid using annotations, but perhaps it’s acceptable for test infrastructure. I need to check the dependency and see if graal-sdk is available.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring serialization options**\\n\\nI’m reconsidering using the Graal `@RegisterForReflection` annotation since it doesn’t seem straightforward. There’s also the `org.graalvm.nativeimage.hosted.FieldValueTransformer`, but no simple register option for Graal. Should I add a test dependency like `org.graalvm.sdk:nativeimage`? But that requires build-time feature registration which I can't do. Perhaps using `RuntimeReflection.register(Object.class.getDeclaredConstructor())` is possible at runtime, but that's not allowed either. I might need to adjust the Bouncy class to avoid requiring a serialization constructor with a serial proxy instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Troubleshooting run errors**\\n\\nI’m thinking about a potential issue after our patch, indicating it’s not related to the current stale native run. The error may come from an old run before metadata generation, which includes our test? But since it relates to our test, that might not make sense. I wonder if the generated metadata files are under build/native/generated. I should check if the Object is configured correctly as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Q5jpJec2sbdK1hlpZEDehcnP|fc_0eeee9a29c5ed17f016a10c63cf97c81939decdc60fe823044", "name": "bash", "argumen